Binary-Numbers.content:
A binary number, b, is an element from a Binary Algebra \mathbb{B}.
Some examples of binary numbers include:

0, from \mathbb{B}
(1,0,0,1) from \mathbb{B}^{4}
(0,0) from \mathbb{B}^{2}

